Well, here we are folks! Our 2017 housing market is well into its 5th month. We have seen rising interest rates and a steady increase of home values, especially in the DMV area. The upward shift in interest rates and values compared to the early part of 2016 is extraordinary, as Michele Lerner from the Washington Post writes, "The number of units sold rose 8.4 percent and the average number of days a property stays on the market decreased by 13 percent. The median home price rose to $464,900, up 2.2 percent in January and February 2017 compared to January and February 2016." With extremely low inventory and they seemingly everlasting threat of rising interest rates, prospective home buyers in our community are acting fast secure their home purchases. Have you thought buying?

We are sipping, socializing, and networking for a cause! 
A portion of the proceeds will go to The Equality Alliance. 
The Equality Alliance will raise money for charities such as Out Youth, LGBT Center, Equality Texas, Kind Clinic, and LGBT against cancer (American Cancer Society). Our Mission

The mission of The Equality Alliance is to give support, aid and reinforcement to organizations that are on the front lines every day fighting for equality and basic human rights for the LGBTQ community. 
Under The Equality Alliance umbrella, charities will not only receive funding but also exposure to new donors that may not be familiar with their work or mission. 
The Equality Alliance is honored to work side by side with local charities with one common goal: Equality 
Our Vision

The Equality Alliance envisions a world where labels are dropped and people are seen as complex, individual human beings.

It is not “gay” marriage – it is marriage.

She is not a “lesbian” mother – she is a mother.. He is not a "homosexual” soldier- he is a soldier. 
She is not a “transgender “judge – she is a judge.

Equality encompasses a lot of things - including the protections against discrimination and the right to feel safe being your true self at home, at work and in the communities around you.

L G B T Q. It is our community. It is a part of who we proudly are. But we are way more than just the sum of some letters – unless those letters are H U M A N. 
It really is just as simple as that.

Want to know how you can get your hands on one of our new Home Buyer/Home Seller handbooks?

It’s really easy...just give us a call and book a no-obligation, complimentary current market evaluation for your home with a member of our Team!

You’ll find out what your home could be worth in today’s #realestate market and we’ll leave you with a copy of our new book - filled with tips to help you get the most when you sell and also help you buy with handy checklists to help you keep track of homes you’ve viewed in your search for a new home.

Inside, we’ll spell out everything you can expect from us as your #Realtors®. How we will help you prepare your home for market; such is #purging, #decluttering and professional #staging and #photography. How we will market and promote your listing online, in print, though our professional connections, open houses and more. 
We provide local market statistics so you can see what’s happening in your area as well as throughout the Region. 
We also introduce you to RE/Max Jazz’s very own baby, WEEMAX Children’s Charities. Every transaction completed by The Rebecca McGarvey Team contributes towards this life-changing, and live-saving, charitable organization exclusive to RE/Max Jazz Agents.  It benefits pediatric patients at Lake Ridge Health Oshawa and other local children’s charities and organization. 
Learn about us - what drives us and makes us tick. We are all passionate about real estate and are true professionals. Rebecca loves to share her knowledge and experience, particularly when it comes to real estate as an #investment and #wealthbuilding tool. 
Handy checklists for before you list right through to closing day and beyond ensure you are on track throughout the whole process.  There’s even a handy list of contact numbers for frequently used services relating to home buying or selling. 
So if you’re thinking of Buying or Selling your Durham Region home in the near future, give Rebecca McGarvey a call at 905-260-4305! It’ll be the best call you make!

Kadi fish market Abuja, Nigeria
One of the most thriving fish markets in Abuja is the Kado Fish Market,located along Gwagwa-Karmo road, Life Camp, it is popular for all kinds of fish products.
It is the first choice for many fish farmers to market their products and fishmongers looking for buyers of their products in the Federal Capital Territory. It is a melting pot and meeting point for fish farmers, businessmen and women dealing in fish and products such as feeds, drugs. 
The market takes care of the various demands of buyers in terms of variety of the products and type of fish desired;whether it is live catfish or smoked ones, buyers are always presented with different choices from which to select.  The market is organised into five segments: those trading in smoked fish, those trading in fresh fish, those selling frozen fish, those who serve as dealers and receive the fish directly from farmers and suppliers, those whose business is preparing the fish for buyers and those selling fish feeds and drugs.
